name: "Dead Boys" custom hand-painted and studded leather jacket
description:
This is a one-of-a-kind.  Pat-t-Shirt was the official screenprinter for Stiv Bators and The Dead Boys-- the image on the jacket was created by Pat, herself!  All of the studding and imaging is hand done.  Be a part of PUNK history out on the streets with this original custom piece!  Size S.

FUN FACT: Stiv Bators is originally from Girard, Ohio and his parents would occasionally babysit Kerri.  She would visit with them when they walked in the Eastwood Mall during the mid 90's and they'd bring cards from John Waters to show her.  Our family sold his shirts up in NYC and in CBGB's during performances and when they would play locally. 

If you would like a custom leather jacket painted/studded like this one or something else-- please contact us through the site.

Each scarf is unique and hand-dyed.  No two are ever the same. These are a simple accessory to add to your outfit!  Warm, washable and comfortably soft. It's hard to just choose ONE!

4 different ways to wear your scarf:
-twisted
-strand of pearls
-loose
-loose loopty
